# SMTP Configuration for Email Service
# Copy this file to .env in the functions directory and fill in your SMTP details

# SMTP Server Configuration
SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_USER=codecollab33@gmail.com
SMTP_PASS=your-app-password-here

# For Gmail:
# 1. Enable 2-factor authentication on your Gmail account
# 2. Generate an App Password: https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords
# 3. Use the generated app password (not your regular password)

# For other email providers:
# - Outlook/Hotmail: smtp-mail.outlook.com, port 587
# - Yahoo: smtp.mail.yahoo.com, port 587
# - Custom SMTP: Use your provider's settings

# Security Notes:
# - Never commit this file to version control
# - Use Firebase environment variables in production
# - Set these via: firebase functions:config:set smtp.host="smtp.gmail.com" smtp.port="587"